<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="218" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="23.[151,1437,1612,1999]" pageId="23" pageNumber="218">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1897" box="[151,260,1613,1639]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Thyraylia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,260,1613,1639]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="218">Thyraylia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[with its synonym 
<taxonomicName authority="Obraztsov, 1944" authorityName="Obraztsov" authorityYear="1944" box="[488,798,1613,1639]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Acornutia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[488,600,1613,1639]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="218">Acornutia</emphasis>
Obraztsov, 1944
</taxonomicName>
; 
<typeStatus box="[813,861,1613,1639]" pageId="23" pageNumber="218">type</typeStatus>
species 
<taxonomicName authority="(Haworth, 1811)" authorityName="Haworth" authorityYear="1811" baseAuthorityName="Haworth" baseAuthorityYear="1811" box="[962,1326,1612,1639]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Cochylis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nana">
<emphasis box="[962,1126,1613,1639]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="218">Cochylis nana</emphasis>
(Haworth, 1811)
</taxonomicName>
] includes seven Nearctic species (including the one transferred herein) and one Holarctic species. Although 
<bibRefCitation author="Razowski, J." box="[1245,1436,1649,1676]" pageId="23" pageNumber="218" pagination="281 - 356" refId="ref20669" refString="Razowski, J. (1960) Studies on the Cochylidae (Lepidoptera). Part II. The genera of the Palaeractic Cochylidae. Polskie Pismo Entomologiczne, 30, 281 - 356." type="journal article" year="1960">Razowski (1960)</bibRefCitation>
treated it as a valid genus (as its junior synonym 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Obraztsov" authorityYear="1944" box="[698,810,1685,1711]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Acornutia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[698,810,1685,1711]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="218">Acornutia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), he later (
<bibRefCitation author="Razowski, J." box="[931,1109,1685,1711]" pageId="23" pageNumber="218" pagination="1 - 528" refId="ref20743" refString="Razowski, J. (1970) Cochylidae. In: Amsel, H. G., Gregor, F. &amp; Reiser, H. (Eds.), Microlepidoptera Palaearctica. Vol. 3. Verlag G. Fromme &amp; Co., Wien, pp. 1 - 528 + i-xxx." type="book chapter" year="1970">Razowski 1970</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Razowski, J." box="[1120,1179,1685,1711]" pageId="23" pageNumber="218" pagination="107 - 163" refId="ref21015" refString="Razowski, J. (1997) Cochylini (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae) of Canada. Acta Zoologica Cracoviensia, 40, 107 - 163." type="journal article" year="1997">1997</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Razowski, J." box="[1190,1247,1685,1711]" pageId="23" pageNumber="218" pagination="397 - 414" refId="ref21041" refString="Razowski, J. (2011) Diagnoses and remarks on genera of Tortricidae, 2. Cochylini (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae). SHILAP Revista de Lepidopterologia, 39, 397 - 414." type="journal article" year="2011">2011</bibRefCitation>
) treated 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Obraztsov" authorityYear="1944" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Acornutia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="218">Acornutia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(which he considered a monotypic genus for the Holarctic species 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Haworth" baseAuthorityYear="1811" box="[946,1002,1722,1747]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Cochylis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nana">
<emphasis box="[946,1002,1722,1747]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="218">nana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Treitschke" authorityYear="1829" box="[1214,1312,1721,1747]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Cochylis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1214,1312,1721,1747]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="218">Cochylis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1897" box="[151,260,1757,1783]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Thyraylia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,260,1757,1783]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="218">Thyraylia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has long been recognized as a valid genus in North America (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Powell, J. A." box="[994,1137,1757,1783]" pageId="23" pageNumber="218" pagination="31 - 42" refId="ref20538" refString="Powell, J. A. (1983) Tortricoidea. In: Hodges, R. W. (Ed.), Check list of the Lepidoptera of America north of Mexico. E. W. Classey, Ltd. and Wedge Entomological Research Foundation, London, pp. 31 - 42." type="book chapter" year="1983">Powell 1983</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pogue, M. G." box="[1147,1281,1757,1783]" pageId="23" pageNumber="218" refId="ref20442" refString="Pogue, M. G. (1986) A generic revision of the Cochylidae (Lepidoptera) of North America. Ph. D. dissertation, University of Minnesota, Minneapolis, Minnesota, 280 pp." type="book" year="1986">Pogue 1986</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Brown, J. W." box="[1291,1432,1756,1783]" pageId="23" pageNumber="218" refId="ref19539" refString="Brown, J. W. (2005) World catalogue of insects. Vol. 5. Tortricidae (Lepidoptera). Apollo Books, Stenstrup, 741 pp." type="book" year="2005">Brown 2005</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Metzler, E. H. &amp; Brown, J. W." box="[151,424,1793,1819]" pageId="23" pageNumber="218" pagination="274 - 282" refId="ref20205" refString="Metzler, E. H. &amp; Brown, J. W. (2014) An updated check list the Cochylina (Tortricidae, Tortricinae, Euliini) of North America north of Mexico including Greenland, with comments on classification and identification. Journal of the Lepidopterists' Society, 68, 274 - 282. https: // doi. org / 10.18473 / lepi. v 68 i 4. a 5" type="journal article" year="2014">Metzler &amp; Brown 2014</bibRefCitation>
), and it currently includes the following species: 
<emphasis box="[992,1048,1793,1819]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="218">bana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kearfott, W. D." box="[1065,1236,1793,1819]" pageId="23" pageNumber="218" pagination="1 - 98" refId="ref20059" refString="Kearfott, W. D. (1907) New North American Tortricidae. Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 33, 1 - 98." type="journal article" year="1907">Kearfott, 1907</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="(Robinson, 1869)" authorityName="Robinson" authorityYear="1869" baseAuthorityName="Robinson" baseAuthorityYear="1869" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Conchylis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bunteana">
<emphasis box="[1257,1361,1793,1819]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="218">bunteana</emphasis>
(Robinson, 1869)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[307,394,1829,1855]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="218">discana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kearfott, W. D." box="[410,580,1829,1855]" pageId="23" pageNumber="218" pagination="1 - 98" refId="ref20059" refString="Kearfott, W. D. (1907) New North American Tortricidae. Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 33, 1 - 98." type="journal article" year="1907">Kearfott, 1907</bibRefCitation>
), 
<emphasis box="[601,707,1830,1855]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="218">gunniana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Busck, A." box="[722,869,1829,1855]" pageId="23" pageNumber="218" pagination="19 - 36" refId="ref19735" refString="Busck, A. (1907) A review of the tortricid subfamily Phaloniinae with descriptions of new American species. Journal of the New York Entomological Society, 15, 19 - 36." type="journal article" year="1907">Busck, 1907</bibRefCitation>
), 
<emphasis box="[889,1017,1829,1855]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="218">hollandana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kearfott, W. D." box="[1033,1203,1829,1855]" pageId="23" pageNumber="218" pagination="1 - 98" refId="ref20059" refString="Kearfott, W. D. (1907) New North American Tortricidae. Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 33, 1 - 98." type="journal article" year="1907">Kearfott, 1907</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Haworth" baseAuthorityYear="1811" box="[1223,1279,1830,1855]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Cochylis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nana">
<emphasis box="[1223,1279,1830,1855]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="218">nana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<emphasis box="[1343,1436,1830,1855]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="218">voxcana</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kearfott, W. D." box="[159,327,1865,1891]" pageId="23" pageNumber="218" pagination="1 - 98" refId="ref20059" refString="Kearfott, W. D. (1907) New North American Tortricidae. Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 33, 1 - 98." type="journal article" year="1907">Kearfott, 1907</bibRefCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Metzler, E. H. &amp; Brown, J. W." box="[352,627,1865,1891]" pageId="23" pageNumber="218" pagination="274 - 282" refId="ref20205" refString="Metzler, E. H. &amp; Brown, J. W. (2014) An updated check list the Cochylina (Tortricidae, Tortricinae, Euliini) of North America north of Mexico including Greenland, with comments on classification and identification. Journal of the Lepidopterists' Society, 68, 274 - 282. https: // doi. org / 10.18473 / lepi. v 68 i 4. a 5" type="journal article" year="2014">Metzler &amp; Brown 2014</bibRefCitation>
). Species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1897" box="[774,883,1865,1891]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Thyraylia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[774,883,1865,1891]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="218">Thyraylia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are characterized by an elongate, somewhat upcurved, distally attenuate valva, a sacculus with a long, free distal tip near the middle of the venter of the valva, and a slender, curved, apically pointed phallus that lacks cornuti (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Razowski, J." box="[896,1073,1937,1963]" pageId="23" pageNumber="218" pagination="107 - 163" refId="ref21015" refString="Razowski, J. (1997) Cochylini (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae) of Canada. Acta Zoologica Cracoviensia, 40, 107 - 163." type="journal article" year="1997">Razowski 1997</bibRefCitation>
: figs. 87‒91). 
<taxonomicName authority="Kearfott" authorityName="Kearfott" authorityYear="1907" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Phalonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wiscana">
<emphasis box="[1234,1436,1937,1963]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="218">Phalonia wiscana</emphasis>
Kearfott
</taxonomicName>
is herein transferred to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1897" box="[511,620,1973,1999]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Thyraylia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="218" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[511,620,1973,1999]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="218">Thyraylia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
